Recently, my spirit bro @100 and I have been getting inquisitively insightful and deep into conversation about life and existence, so I thought to send him a song that resonated with me on an intrinsic level. 

It's called DANCE by CLMD & Tungevaag.

I'm not too much of a dancer (publically), but I believe dancing is another form of art and self-expression. Not gonna lie, when I'm by myself and start to enter a FLOW state, dancing becomes my best form of self-liberation and may even overtake what I'm doing at that very moment to pull me into this trance of simply existing within that very moment.

"The meaning and purpose of dancing is the dance. Like music also, it is fulfilled in each moment of its course. You do not play a sonata in order to reach the final chord, and if the meaning of things were simply in ends, composers would write nothing but finales." - Alan Watts
